{
  "texts": [
    "P p = {↓x | x ∈ S} ∪ {∅}, where ↓x = {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ x}; 6. π(p) = ↓θ(p) = {x ∈ S | x ⊑ θ(p)}.",
    "◁The following property of A u /A p when A is a T -BAO will be useful later.Lemma 5.15 (Full/Principal Frame of a T -BAO).",
    "For any T -BAO A, A u /A p is such that for all x, y ∈ S, xR i y iff y ⊑ f i (x), where f i is the left adjoint of ■ i (recall Definition 5.1.4).Proof.",
    "If we do not have xR i y, then there is a y ′ such that ⊥ ̸ = y ′ ⊑ y andx ∧ ♦ i y ′ = ⊥, so x ⊑ ■ i -y ′.",
    "Hence f i (x) ⊑ -y ′, which with ⊥ ̸ = y ′ implies y ′ ̸ ⊑ f i (x), which with y ′ ⊑ y implies y ̸ ⊑ f i (x)."
  ]
}